         <abstract>
            <p>In a rising market, average return increases as the quality of individual issues declines. On the other hand, whereas the level of return variability falls as the number of issues held in a portfolio increases, average return is unaffected. Hence the investor is better off holding a large number of low quality stocks than a smaller number of high quality stocks; return on the former portfolio will be higher for a given level of over-all price variability.</p>
          </abstract>
